BIG EAST CONFERENCE MEN'S TOURNAMENT
March 9, 2005
John Allen
Donald Copeland
Louis Orr
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









<p>	Q.  Louis, I know we've asked this before, can you put your finger on what went wrong offensively late in the game? </p>
<p>	Q.  Will you say anything to Justin?  You took him out after the turnover there, 30 seconds left.  He's a kid that's going forward, is part of your future.  What do you say to a kid like that? </p>
<p>	Q.  John, have you thought about the finality?  What are your emotions right now? </p>

<p>	Q.  This is for Don.  How were you physically in the second half? </p>
<p>	Q.  I guess offensively and defensively, was it a matter of not executing? </p>
<p>	Q.  Coach, as you mentioned, the last two games are the best the team has played.  The last five minutes, are you able to build off of what you did the last two games despite the last five minutes for next year? </p>
<p>	Q.  Can you put your finger on what was wrong with Kelly, what was bothering Kelly tonight? </p>
<p>	Q.  This is really for everyone.  This was another close loss, you weren't able to close it out at the end of the game.  How frustrating was it throughout the year to have so many of those games that are coming down to the wire, to not be able to close it out at the end?</p>



